##date columns are handled in each table 

1. In silver.crm_cust_info

Column: cst_create_date

âœ… What happens:
This column is copied directly from the bronze table â€” no transformation, just preserved.

Reason: Itâ€™s a proper datetime column already (used to identify the latest record).
The filtering step ensures we keep only the latest entry per customer:

ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY cst_id ORDER BY cst_create_date DESC)


So even though itâ€™s not cleaned, itâ€™s used for logic.

ğŸ§­ 2. In silver.crm_prd_info

Columns: prd_start_dt, prd_end_dt

âœ… What happens:

CAST(prd_start_dt AS DATE) AS prd_start_dt,
CAST(LEAD(prd_start_dt) OVER (...) - 1 AS DATE) AS prd_end_dt


Explanation:

Converts prd_start_dt into a proper SQL DATE format.

Calculates prd_end_dt as one day before the next productâ€™s start date, using the LEAD() function.

ğŸ§  Purpose:
Ensures each productâ€™s validity period (start â†’ end) has no overlaps and follows chronological order.

ğŸ§­ 3. In silver.crm_sales_details

Columns: sls_order_dt, sls_ship_dt, sls_due_dt

âœ… What happens:
Each of these date columns is validated and corrected:

CASE 
    WHEN sls_order_dt = 0 OR LEN(sls_order_dt) != 8 THEN NULL
    ELSE CAST(CAST(sls_order_dt AS VARCHAR) AS DATE)
END AS sls_order_dt


Explanation:

If the value is 0 or not an 8-digit number (like 20250123), it becomes NULL.

If itâ€™s valid (e.g. 20250123), itâ€™s cast to a proper DATE (2025-01-23).

ğŸ§  Purpose:
Avoids invalid dates that would break reports or calculations.
E.g. 00000000 or 99999999 becomes NULL instead of causing an error.

ğŸ§­ 4. In silver.erp_cust_az12

Column: bdate (birth date)

âœ… What happens:

CASE WHEN bdate > GETDATE() THEN NULL ELSE bdate END AS bdate


Explanation:
If the birthdate is in the future (like 2050-05-10), itâ€™s clearly wrong â†’ set to NULL.

ğŸ§  Purpose:
Ensures the data makes logical sense.
You canâ€™t have a birthdate greater than today.

ğŸ§¾ Summary Table
Table	Date Columns	Validation / Transformation	Why
crm_cust_info	cst_create_date	Used for finding latest record	Ensures only latest record is loaded
crm_prd_info	prd_start_dt, prd_end_dt	Cast to DATE, prd_end_dt = next start date âˆ’ 1	Maintains valid product date ranges
crm_sales_details	sls_order_dt, sls_ship_dt, sls_due_dt	Invalid (0 or wrong length) â†’ NULL	Cleans and standardizes date fields
erp_cust_az12	bdate	Future date â†’ NULL	Removes logically invalid birthdates
âœ³ï¸ Why All This Matters

## If you donâ€™t clean date columns:

Queries like WHERE order_date BETWEEN ... might fail or return wrong results.

Charts in Power BI or dashboards might crash due to invalid date formats.

Analytics (like monthly sales trends) would show inconsistent data.
